SIMPLE: invertible
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Invertible
<hw>In*vert"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Invert</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Capable of being inverted or
turned inside out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Capable of being changed or
converted; <as>as, <ex>invertible</ex> sugar</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invertible</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Invertible
<hw>In*vert"i*ble</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>in-</ets> not +
L. <ets>vertere</ets> to turn + <ets>-ible</ets>.]</ety> <def>Incapable
of being turned or changed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An indurate and <qex>invertible</qex> conscience.</q>
<rj><qau>Cranmer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invertin</ent>⟦br⟧
